<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-01-10T17:40:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-01-10T17:40:00-05:00" n="351" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d351">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.00–1374</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Russell</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-01-10T18:00:00-04:40">
                                    <hi rend="italic">January 10, 1916, 6 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Foreign Office has just advised me of a cable received from Dominican
                            Legation, Port au Prince, dated eighth, as follows: Armed manifestation
                            against Americans, several important arrests, grave events awaited.
                            Dominican Minister left.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Russell</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>